  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria are:

          1. 3-16 years old

          2. diagnosed with congenital hemiplegic or CP with one more affected side

          3. considerable nonuse of the affected upper limb.

        Exclusion criteria are:

          1. no excessive muscle tone (Modified Ashworth Scale â‰¤ 2 at any joints of the upper limb)
             before beginning treatment (Bohannon &amp; Smith, 1987)

          2. no severe cognitive, visual, or auditory disorders according to medical documents,
             parental reports, and the examiner's clinical observation

          3. no injections of botulinum toxin type A or operations on the upper limb within 6
             months.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
